snippet: The Internet services provider, which is known for its provocative television commercials, plans to sell shares between $17 and $19 a share.
abstract: DealBook Online; Internet services provider GoDaddy says it plans to sell shares in its initial public offering priced between $17 and $19 a share, valuing company at midpoint at $2.72 billion.
lead_paragraph: The Internet services provider, which is known for its provocative television commercials, plans to sell shares between $17 and $19 a share.

headline.main: GoDaddy Sets Price Range for I.P.O.
